{"key":"post-13242611","value":"<?xml version=\"1.0\"?>\n<post>\n<id>13242611</id>\n<content>Ants are easy to get rid of.&amp;nbsp; Simply place some small containers out with a mixture of Borax and karo syrup.&amp;nbsp; Mix about 1 teaspoon of 20 mule team borax into roughly 1/4 cup of karo or even sugar water.&amp;nbsp; Put it where they can easily get to it to drink.&amp;nbsp; They'll lay a scent trail to the bait and in a few days you'll have hundreds of ants feeding from the little trap you've set.&amp;nbsp; However, in a week or so they'll be gone.&amp;nbsp; They take the borax back to the nest and feed it to their young and the queen, and it kills the colony from the inside.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Best of all it's non toxic to anything but ants and termites.&lt;br /&gt;RR</content>\n<name>RogerRabbit</name>\n<next>13242621</next>\n<prev>13242584</prev>\n<first>13241879</first>\n<last>13242967</last>\n<when>1285385536</when>\n<utime>09/25/10 06:32 AM</utime>\n</post>"}